1
00:00:36,833 --> 00:00:38,633
<i> So, is this our new house?</i>

2
00:00:38,767 --> 00:00:40,100
<i>Who are you going to keep here?</i>

3
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:41,200
<i> Your mistress?</i>

4
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:42,500
<i>- Hazel!
- Stop!</i>

5
00:00:42,633 --> 00:00:45,067
<i> I said stop!</i>

6
00:00:46,533 --> 00:00:49,400
<i>- I'm so done with you!
- Bro, bro, bro, don't!</i>

7
00:00:49,533 --> 00:00:52,067
<i> Dad, I've decided.</i>

8
00:00:52,200 --> 00:00:54,367
<i> I'll go with Mom for now.</i>

9
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:57,700
<i>I don't understand why Jessica
made such a decision, Felma.</i>

10
00:00:57,833 --> 00:01:00,033
<i> Hazel did something.</i>

11
00:01:02,300 --> 00:01:04,167
<i> Answer your sister's call.</i>

12
00:01:04,300 --> 00:01:05,500
<i> It might be an emergency.</i>

13
00:01:05,633 --> 00:01:06,467
<i> I don't care.</i>

14
00:01:06,600 --> 00:01:08,500
<i> Andrea, please answer.</i>

15
00:01:08,667 --> 00:01:10,000
<i> Jeff is back.</i>

16
00:01:10,133 --> 00:01:11,433
<i> Daisy left him.</i>

17
00:01:11,567 --> 00:01:12,800
<i> She took Tetay with her.</i>

18
00:01:12,933 --> 00:01:16,867
<i>He says he's okay,
but he gets drunk every night.</i>

19
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:18,500
<i> I'm worried.</i>

20
00:01:18,867 --> 00:01:20,900
<i> Jeffrey went back home?</i>

21
00:01:21,033 --> 00:01:22,267
<i> So you know how painful it is.</i>

22
00:01:22,400 --> 00:01:23,500
<i> But why did you leave us?</i>

23
00:01:23,633 --> 00:01:25,167
<i> Because I'm a jerk!</i>

24
00:01:25,300 --> 00:01:27,167
<i> I'm a jerk, Jeff!</i>

25
00:01:27,300 --> 00:01:29,100
<i> I made a mistake one night.</i>

26
00:01:29,233 --> 00:01:31,300
<i>But I've regretted it
every single day of my life.</i>

27
00:01:31,433 --> 00:01:33,433
<i>I said don't touch me!
I don't need you!</i>

28
00:01:33,567 --> 00:01:35,333
<i> Can't you understand that?</i>

29
00:01:37,767 --> 00:01:38,833
Jeff!

30
00:01:39,700 --> 00:01:40,700
Help!

31
00:01:41,233 --> 00:01:42,433
Help! Jeff!

32
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:44,133
Help! Felma!

33
00:01:48,167 --> 00:01:49,200
Jeff!

34
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,400
Jeff, hold on to it!

35
00:01:55,167 --> 00:01:56,700
Yes, Colonel.

36
00:01:56,833 --> 00:01:58,933
Hi, I just wanted
to follow up on my request

37
00:01:59,067 --> 00:02:01,600
regarding Jeffrey's child.

38
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,833
Maybe you've heard something

39
00:02:02,967 --> 00:02:07,267
from the Immigration Authority
and the Overseas Bureau?

40
00:02:09,267 --> 00:02:10,767
Alright, thank you.

41
00:02:11,667 --> 00:02:13,333
Please let me know as soon
as you receive any updates.

42
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:22,367
Jeffrey!

43
00:02:23,967 --> 00:02:25,867
Jeffery, hold on to it!

44
00:02:32,333 --> 00:02:33,767
Felma!

45
00:02:34,967 --> 00:02:37,033
Jeffrey, grab it! Jeff!

46
00:02:40,933 --> 00:02:43,233
Jeffrey! Jeffrey, grab it!

47
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:47,933
Felma!

48
00:02:54,200 --> 00:02:55,200
Grab it!

49
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:57,567
Hold on to it!

50
00:03:06,767 --> 00:03:07,867
Manuel?

51
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,867
Manuel, what's going on?

52
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:11,433
Manuel! Jeff!

53
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:12,833
Jeff!

54
00:03:13,100 --> 00:03:13,633
Son!

55
00:03:18,833 --> 00:03:20,033
Son!

56
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:32,633
- Grab Jeff!
- Jeffrey!

57
00:04:00,767 --> 00:04:04,467
It hasn't even been a day,
and you already miss your dad?

58
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:05,867
What?

59
00:04:06,767 --> 00:04:08,267
He's not answering you?

60
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:12,333
Mom,

61
00:04:12,467 --> 00:04:16,433
can I go stay
with Dad for a while?

62
00:04:16,567 --> 00:04:19,467
I just feel like
he's upset with me.

63
00:04:19,600 --> 00:04:22,033
Because I chose
to stay with you.

64
00:04:23,367 --> 00:04:25,633
So you're worried
about his feelings?

65
00:04:25,767 --> 00:04:27,433
But did it ever cross your
mind how pissed off I am

66
00:04:27,600 --> 00:04:29,133
at how you're acting?

67
00:04:30,000 --> 00:04:31,833
Mom, come on.

68
00:04:33,600 --> 00:04:34,833
What?

69
00:04:36,000 --> 00:04:38,267
You've been calling,
and he won't pick up?

70
00:04:38,400 --> 00:04:39,933
You're worried?

71
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:43,000
Maybe he's just busy.

72
00:04:43,133 --> 00:04:46,100
Busy bonding with
his other family.

73
00:04:46,233 --> 00:04:48,133
Mom, you're not helping.

74
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:51,100
There you go again.

75
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:54,300
Why do you always assume
the worst about me?

76
00:04:54,433 --> 00:04:56,533
Honestly,
I just want to help you.

77
00:04:56,667 --> 00:04:58,500
You just don't see it.

78
00:04:59,367 --> 00:05:00,833
Think about it.

79
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:07,100
You're calling your dad,
and either he doesn't miss you

80
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:09,767
or he just doesn't
want to pick up.

81
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:13,733
You know what? If I were you,
I'd start learning that your dad

82
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:16,100
isn't always going to
be there beside you.

83
00:05:17,600 --> 00:05:19,100
Mom, please.

84
00:05:21,900 --> 00:05:23,267
Now you know the feeling.

85
00:05:24,267 --> 00:05:27,400
That's exactly how you
and your dad made me feel.

86
00:05:28,900 --> 00:05:30,100
Okay.

87
00:05:31,233 --> 00:05:32,967
You want to go visit your dad?

88
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:34,100
Go ahead.

89
00:05:34,933 --> 00:05:37,100
I don't want you to think
that I'm such a bad person.

90
00:05:37,233 --> 00:05:40,000
Really, Mom? Thank you.

91
00:05:40,133 --> 00:05:41,367
Yes,

92
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:44,433
but you'll be my eyes
and ears at your dad's place,

93
00:05:44,567 --> 00:05:47,100
and report everything to me.
Do you understand?

94
00:05:49,467 --> 00:05:54,067
I'll let you go,
but your loyalty stays with me.

95
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,800
Because if not,

96
00:05:57,633 --> 00:06:01,867
I can reveal
your secret any time.

97
00:06:32,400 --> 00:06:33,900
I'm sorry, the subscriber...

98
00:06:34,033 --> 00:06:37,133
Elvie, please. Elvie.

99
00:06:38,233 --> 00:06:39,267
I'm sorry, the subscriber...

100
00:06:39,400 --> 00:06:41,467
- What's going on?
- Andrea.

101
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:44,133
Come on.

102
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:46,800
You've been calling non-stop.

103
00:06:47,100 --> 00:06:49,600
Miss Elvie can't be reached,
right?

104
00:06:50,167 --> 00:06:53,733
She's not answering.
She ran off with my investment!

105
00:06:56,433 --> 00:06:59,033
Or maybe you're calling
the wrong person?

106
00:07:01,133 --> 00:07:04,633
Sonny, I'm sorry. I really
can't reach Elvie either.

107
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:09,300
I'm worried about
my sibling, too.

108
00:07:09,433 --> 00:07:11,400
We both have problems.

109
00:07:11,533 --> 00:07:14,500
Why? Does your sibling's life
depend on this?

110
00:07:14,667 --> 00:07:17,333
Mine does. For me,
it's my child's life.

111
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:21,067
Andrea, I don't have money for
medicine. I'm completely broke.

112
00:07:21,200 --> 00:07:22,067
And you're the one who got me

113
00:07:22,200 --> 00:07:23,333
into that lending company,
right?

114
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:24,767
So give me my money back.

115
00:07:24,900 --> 00:07:26,400
Sonny, hold on.

116
00:07:26,533 --> 00:07:29,233
We're both waiting.
I don't have money either.

117
00:07:29,800 --> 00:07:31,100
How much do you need?

118
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:32,767
50,000 pesos.

119
00:07:32,900 --> 00:07:34,900
- Okay.
- No, wait!

120
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:36,567
You can't do it.

121
00:07:36,700 --> 00:07:38,500
You don't have anything
to do with this, Joel.

122
00:07:38,867 --> 00:07:39,833
I'm sorry, Sonny.

123
00:07:39,967 --> 00:07:41,967
I don't have the money either,
but...

124
00:07:42,900 --> 00:07:44,333
Here, wait.

125
00:07:48,367 --> 00:07:51,467
This is all I have.
But I hope it helps.

126
00:07:55,667 --> 00:07:56,867
What is this?

127
00:07:57,500 --> 00:07:59,367
Andrea, this is way too little.

128
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:02,233
I can't even buy my child's
medicine with this.

129
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:05,667
I know, but once I get
in touch with Elvie,

130
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,700
- I'm sure I can get more...
- When?

131
00:08:09,633 --> 00:08:10,833
When are you going
to talk to her?

132
00:08:10,967 --> 00:08:13,567
My child is about to die, and I
still can't afford the medicine.

133
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:15,467
Just tell me when.

134
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:17,333
- Because I need that money.
- Hold on. Hello?

135
00:08:18,467 --> 00:08:19,500
What?

136
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,067
Where's Jeff??

137
00:08:24,267 --> 00:08:25,500
What?

138
00:08:30,433 --> 00:08:33,133
Jeffrey almost drowned
because he was drunk.

139
00:08:33,267 --> 00:08:35,267
It's a good thing...

140
00:08:35,400 --> 00:08:36,467
Andrea?

141
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,767
Hello!

142
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,833
Why did you do that?

143
00:08:49,767 --> 00:08:51,933
Why did you throw yourself
into the pool to save me?

144
00:08:52,067 --> 00:08:53,833
You knew how dangerous
that was for you.

145
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:56,100
If any of my children
are in danger,

146
00:08:56,233 --> 00:08:58,567
I wouldn't hesitate to save
them.

147
00:08:59,100 --> 00:09:00,733
Even if it costs me my life.

148
00:09:03,733 --> 00:09:04,500
Dad.

149
00:09:05,033 --> 00:09:06,333
Sorry.

150
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,233
I'm sorry.

151
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:19,767
I understand.

152
00:09:21,967 --> 00:09:24,100
I understand, son.

153
00:09:28,667 --> 00:09:31,900
I've made such a huge mistake
with all of you.

154
00:09:35,500 --> 00:09:37,667
I hope you can forgive me.

155
00:09:40,167 --> 00:09:42,133
Please, forgive me.

156
00:10:03,233 --> 00:10:04,600
You know, dear...

157
00:10:05,233 --> 00:10:06,633
I still can't believe it.

158
00:10:06,767 --> 00:10:09,100
Your big brother has
already forgiven me.

159
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:17,467
Why are you so quiet?

160
00:10:19,700 --> 00:10:22,600
Why do you look like that?
Is something wrong?

161
00:10:24,533 --> 00:10:26,400
Dad, it's you.

162
00:10:26,933 --> 00:10:28,933
You're the problem.

163
00:10:29,067 --> 00:10:32,300
You risked your life again.
You saved someone

164
00:10:32,433 --> 00:10:35,567
without thinking about
the danger to yourself.

165
00:10:35,733 --> 00:10:38,667
But your brother
was about to drown.

166
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,200
And you, Dad?

167
00:10:40,333 --> 00:10:44,233
Didn't you think you
could have drowned, too?

168
00:10:44,367 --> 00:10:47,133
Dad, you've already
risked your life before.

169
00:10:47,267 --> 00:10:49,400
And look what happened.

170
00:10:49,533 --> 00:10:52,400
You became a paraplegic.

171
00:10:54,100 --> 00:10:56,967
I don't want to sound selfish,

172
00:10:57,100 --> 00:10:58,600
but Dad,

173
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:02,367
save something for yourself.

174
00:11:02,500 --> 00:11:04,200
Save something for me.

175
00:11:06,900 --> 00:11:11,267
What's going to happen
to me if you're gone?

176
00:11:12,567 --> 00:11:15,433
I can't bear losing you, Dad.

177
00:11:18,233 --> 00:11:19,333
Sweetie.

178
00:11:19,467 --> 00:11:21,067
Dear, I'm sorry.

179
00:11:22,233 --> 00:11:26,533
I'm sorry, but that's
just how fathers are.

180
00:11:27,167 --> 00:11:30,833
We'd put our own lives on
the line for our children.

181
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,233
Even if it happened to you,
I'd do the same.

182
00:11:35,367 --> 00:11:37,467
I wouldn't hesitate.

183
00:11:39,433 --> 00:11:40,967
Of course,

184
00:11:41,100 --> 00:11:44,933
you're all my blood and flesh.
I won't let you get hurt.

185
00:11:47,067 --> 00:11:50,000
<i> So, the man you look up to?</i>

186
00:11:50,133 --> 00:11:54,633
<i>He's not even related to you.
He's not your blood.</i>

187
00:11:55,933 --> 00:11:57,967
Enough, okay?
Please, stop crying now.

188
00:11:58,533 --> 00:12:02,000
It's okay, dear,
stop crying now.

189
00:12:10,900 --> 00:12:13,333
I don't want to go in, Jeff.

190
00:12:13,467 --> 00:12:15,600
Where are you? Come out now.

191
00:12:18,000 --> 00:12:19,000
I'm coming.

192
00:12:22,533 --> 00:12:24,067
What happened?

193
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:26,367
Where did it hit you?

194
00:12:26,500 --> 00:12:28,433
Do you have an injury?
Are you okay?

195
00:12:28,867 --> 00:12:30,533
You almost drowned, right?

196
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:32,433
I told you to get checked.
I read something.

197
00:12:32,567 --> 00:12:34,467
If you drown, you still
need to see a doctor.

198
00:12:34,600 --> 00:12:37,467
If you don't,
it can affect your lungs.

199
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:39,667
Andrea,
can you please calm down?

200
00:12:39,800 --> 00:12:42,167
Correction, I almost drowned.

201
00:12:42,300 --> 00:12:43,767
But they managed to save me.

202
00:12:45,700 --> 00:12:47,500
I was saved. I'm okay.

203
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:48,700
Andrea!

204
00:12:50,667 --> 00:12:52,433
Andrea, did you
know what happened?

205
00:12:52,567 --> 00:12:54,833
Dad saved Jeffrey earlier.

206
00:12:54,967 --> 00:12:56,700
He jumped into the pool
without thinking,

207
00:12:56,833 --> 00:12:58,733
just to pull him out.

208
00:13:00,767 --> 00:13:04,600
Yeah, if it weren't for Dad...

209
00:13:04,733 --> 00:13:07,133
maybe I would've really drowned.

210
00:13:12,667 --> 00:13:14,200
Have you reconciled with him?

211
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:19,033
Andrea.

212
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,600
Joel, come on. Let's go.

213
00:13:21,767 --> 00:13:23,567
Andrea, you should talk first.

214
00:13:23,700 --> 00:13:26,067
Let's go! Come on!

215
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,367
Andrea, let's talk.

216
00:13:29,000 --> 00:13:31,200
Andrea, talk to me first.

217
00:13:31,333 --> 00:13:33,267
Hear me out.

218
00:13:35,900 --> 00:13:36,967
Andrea...

219
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:38,800
Let's go, Joel!

220
00:13:43,833 --> 00:13:45,433
Andrea!

221
00:13:45,967 --> 00:13:47,633
Andrea!

222
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:01,700
Andrea, pick up.

223
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:03,133
Kids!

224
00:14:03,267 --> 00:14:08,000
Kids, where's Andrea?
Didang said she came.

225
00:14:09,467 --> 00:14:11,133
She already left, Mom.

226
00:14:12,900 --> 00:14:14,433
Is that so?

227
00:14:14,567 --> 00:14:16,800
Why didn't she come inside?

228
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:20,767
We could've seen each other.
I miss her so much.

229
00:14:21,467 --> 00:14:23,667
Why was she in such a hurry?

230
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:26,733
No, Mom.

231
00:14:27,300 --> 00:14:32,100
She left because she found out
that Jeff and Dad had made up.

232
00:14:37,767 --> 00:14:39,033
It's okay.

233
00:14:39,500 --> 00:14:43,033
Sooner or later, your sister's
heart will soften.

234
00:14:51,967 --> 00:14:54,433
I was so worried about Jeff.

235
00:14:55,567 --> 00:14:57,533
Turns out, he's fine.

236
00:14:59,233 --> 00:15:00,733
Smiling even.

237
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:04,100
Because he and his father
are okay now.

238
00:15:10,267 --> 00:15:12,000
Jeff...

239
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:16,067
The one who was on my side.

240
00:15:19,033 --> 00:15:22,400
He betrayed me, too,
just like Mom and Coleen did.

241
00:15:26,667 --> 00:15:30,167
They ganged up on me!
They left me all alone!

242
00:15:31,700 --> 00:15:33,567
They're letting themselves
be fooled by the same man

243
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:36,300
who destroyed our family!

244
00:15:37,700 --> 00:15:39,567
Am I wrong, Joel?

245
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,333
Is what I'm feeling wrong?

246
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,833
Am I the one who's wrong?

247
00:15:48,467 --> 00:15:53,233
I don't want to invalidate
what you're feeling.

248
00:15:55,100 --> 00:15:57,333
But Andrea,
please don't get mad.

249
00:15:58,433 --> 00:15:59,900
Don't you think...

250
00:16:01,433 --> 00:16:03,533
you've been too unrelenting?

251
00:16:04,500 --> 00:16:05,767
I mean,

252
00:16:07,433 --> 00:16:09,567
if you really
can't forgive your dad,

253
00:16:09,733 --> 00:16:12,833
even after all the times he's
tried to make things right...

254
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:16,200
Maybe it's time to reconsider.

255
00:16:22,833 --> 00:16:23,867
Okay?

256
00:16:25,433 --> 00:16:29,633
Not every broken family gets
the chance to be whole again.

257
00:16:32,867 --> 00:16:35,333
Don't throw this chance away.

258
00:16:42,000 --> 00:16:44,433
Andrea, come on. Come back.

259
00:16:44,567 --> 00:16:45,967
Let's talk.

260
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:48,767
Coleen and I are outside.
We'll wait for you.

261
00:17:01,933 --> 00:17:03,700
Coleen, stop it already.

262
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:09,567
I'm just looking for
a falling star because...

263
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:12,967
Believe me, Jeff,
wishing on one really works.

264
00:17:13,100 --> 00:17:16,033
I used to wish that you
and Dad would make up.

265
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:18,400
It came true, didn't it?

266
00:17:20,867 --> 00:17:23,467
I just hope you didn't
wish we'd have

267
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:26,867
to nearly die
before it happened?

268
00:17:28,233 --> 00:17:29,767
I'll admit it.

269
00:17:32,033 --> 00:17:34,833
I've wanted to forgive
Dad for a long time.

270
00:17:36,267 --> 00:17:37,933
Especially

271
00:17:38,633 --> 00:17:40,733
if it were Mom asking me to.

272
00:17:44,167 --> 00:17:45,767
But I just couldn't.

273
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,067
You know it was still too heavy.

274
00:17:52,233 --> 00:17:53,767
But when...

275
00:17:54,733 --> 00:17:59,767
I saw what he did to save me...

276
00:18:00,267 --> 00:18:01,900
<i> Jeffrey!</i>

277
00:18:02,033 --> 00:18:03,900
<i> Jeffrey, grab it!</i>

278
00:18:04,633 --> 00:18:06,300
That panic in his voice.

279
00:18:07,567 --> 00:18:09,433
That fear.

280
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:14,633
He just jumped into
the pool without hesitation.

281
00:18:14,767 --> 00:18:16,200
<i> Hold on to it!</i>

282
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:19,667
<i> Hold on! Jeff!</i>

283
00:18:20,733 --> 00:18:23,033
I now know how you feel.

284
00:18:25,533 --> 00:18:28,700
In that moment, I realized
how much he truly loves me.

285
00:18:30,133 --> 00:18:32,900
He didn't think about himself,
his condition.

286
00:18:33,667 --> 00:18:35,367
I was the one who got scared.

287
00:18:36,867 --> 00:18:39,167
Because I realized
I don't want to lose Dad.

288
00:18:41,067 --> 00:18:42,667
If something happened
to him

289
00:18:42,800 --> 00:18:45,367
and I never even got
the chance to say I love him...

290
00:18:45,967 --> 00:18:49,000
I was angry. So angry.
But I love him so much.

291
00:18:50,533 --> 00:18:53,400
It was wrong that I let
my pride get in the way.

292
00:18:56,633 --> 00:18:59,933
And now, I know I need
to make it up with Dad.

293
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:03,167
As well as for Mom.

294
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,233
Felma.

295
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:17,467
You look deep in thought.

296
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:23,033
I can't stop thinking
about what happened earlier.

297
00:19:25,833 --> 00:19:27,633
If we hadn't come,

298
00:19:28,967 --> 00:19:30,433
you could've drowned.

299
00:19:32,700 --> 00:19:36,100
Like I told Jeffrey and Jessica,

300
00:19:37,533 --> 00:19:40,067
I'm ready to die
for my children.

301
00:19:40,833 --> 00:19:43,267
Don't talk like that.

302
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,133
You're giving me chills.

303
00:19:46,933 --> 00:19:48,800
You can't die yet.

304
00:19:50,267 --> 00:19:51,800
I really can't.

305
00:19:51,933 --> 00:19:54,433
Not until Andrea
and I make peace.

306
00:19:55,700 --> 00:19:57,167
But you know what?

307
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:01,133
I'm really happy that
Jeffrey and I finally did.

308
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:04,433
I waited so long
for that moment.

309
00:20:04,567 --> 00:20:08,833
That's why I believe, someday,
Andrea will forgive me, too.

310
00:20:09,667 --> 00:20:11,400
I also pray for that.

311
00:20:12,433 --> 00:20:13,900
And I also hope...

312
00:20:16,300 --> 00:20:20,533
the annulment with Hazel
finally gets approved.

313
00:20:21,867 --> 00:20:23,800
So I can marry you.

314
00:20:24,533 --> 00:20:27,867
And tell the whole world
how much I love you.

315
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,700
Manuel,

316
00:20:31,567 --> 00:20:33,767
take care
of the annulment first.

317
00:20:41,733 --> 00:20:43,700
It's not just them.

318
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:46,267
You have to make it up to me,
too.

319
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:49,467
No more being grumpy with me.
Ever.

320
00:20:51,967 --> 00:20:54,567
Jeff, we should look
for a falling star.

321
00:20:54,700 --> 00:20:59,167
Then we'll both make a wish that
Andrea and Dad will make up too.

322
00:21:01,633 --> 00:21:04,333
Okay. I'll tell you
if I see one first.

323
00:21:06,867 --> 00:21:08,200
But promise me you'll wish
for me, too,

324
00:21:08,367 --> 00:21:10,133
that Andrea will forgive me.

325
00:21:10,267 --> 00:21:13,900
I hope she stop being mad at me.
She's always mad at me.

326
00:21:14,233 --> 00:21:16,833
Of course, Jeff.
That's automatic, you know?

327
00:21:18,600 --> 00:21:23,333
But I really hope we can be
a complete family again.

328
00:21:25,433 --> 00:21:29,033
But even if we become
a complete family,

329
00:21:29,167 --> 00:21:31,067
I don't think we'll ever
really be happy.

330
00:21:32,233 --> 00:21:34,467
Because we're still
not the legal family.

331
00:21:35,467 --> 00:21:37,700
Not until Dad's marriage
to Hazel is annulled.

332
00:21:37,833 --> 00:21:40,267
We don't want Mom to be
the other woman, right?

333
00:21:41,100 --> 00:21:43,167
Of course not.

334
00:21:43,700 --> 00:21:47,700
What was the point of Mom's
viral statement saying,

335
00:21:47,833 --> 00:21:52,133
"I am Felma Ruiz.
I am not a mistress.

336
00:21:52,267 --> 00:21:54,733
I was never a mistress.

337
00:21:54,867 --> 00:21:58,600
And I will never be one."

338
00:22:00,867 --> 00:22:02,333
You know what?
I should've recorded you!

339
00:22:02,467 --> 00:22:03,533
So I could show it to Mom.

340
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:06,367
- Am I good?
- That was so intense.

341
00:22:07,233 --> 00:22:08,967
But, Jeffrey, seriously...

342
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:13,233
What if Dad's marriage
to Hazel finally gets annulled?

343
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:15,000
And then...

344
00:22:15,467 --> 00:22:18,000
I hope, because this is one
of my wishes,

345
00:22:18,133 --> 00:22:20,267
I hope that Dad and Mom
get back together.

346
00:22:21,433 --> 00:22:23,067
But what about Jessica?

347
00:22:27,167 --> 00:22:28,500
I don't know.

348
00:22:30,900 --> 00:22:33,133
I really don't know.

349
00:22:34,100 --> 00:22:35,200
All I'm saying is she should
stay with her real mother.

350
00:22:35,333 --> 00:22:39,000
Hazel's her real mother anyway,
not Mom.

351
00:22:40,033 --> 00:22:42,700
She should just
go back to her.

352
00:22:44,600 --> 00:22:46,400
You know what, Jeff?

353
00:22:46,767 --> 00:22:47,967
Same here.

354
00:22:49,167 --> 00:22:53,133
I mean, it's fine if she
visits Dad sometimes.

355
00:22:53,533 --> 00:22:54,767
But...

356
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:58,433
I don't want her
to be part of our family.

357
00:23:14,067 --> 00:23:17,567
<i>What if Dad's marriage
to Hazel finally gets annulled,</i>

358
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:21,233
<i>and he and Mom
get back together?</i>

359
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:22,567
<i>What happens to
Jessica then?</i>

360
00:23:22,700 --> 00:23:23,800
<i>She should stay with
her real mother.</i>

361
00:23:23,933 --> 00:23:26,933
<i>Hazel's her real mother anyway,
not Mom.</i>

362
00:23:27,067 --> 00:23:28,700
<i>She should just
go back to her.</i>

363
00:23:28,833 --> 00:23:32,033
<i>It's fine if she
visits Dad sometimes.</i>

364
00:23:32,167 --> 00:23:37,133
<i>But I don't want her to
be part of our family.</i>

365
00:23:37,267 --> 00:23:39,833
It's all clear now, Dad...

366
00:23:41,467 --> 00:23:44,167
They really don't want me.

367
00:23:45,567 --> 00:23:48,667
How much more if they learned
the truth....

368
00:23:54,267 --> 00:23:57,100
What if they stop you ...

369
00:23:58,933 --> 00:24:01,067
from visiting me.

370
00:24:01,867 --> 00:24:04,633
I don't want that
to happen, Dad.

371
00:24:06,100 --> 00:24:08,700
I don't want to
be pushed away.

372
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:16,167
I don't want them to take
you away from me, Dad.

373
00:24:17,300 --> 00:24:19,233
Not now.

374
00:24:20,200 --> 00:24:22,267
Not ever.

375
00:24:34,867 --> 00:24:35,933
What?

376
00:24:36,800 --> 00:24:39,100
So Manuel and his eldest
have made up?

377
00:24:39,233 --> 00:24:40,900
Yes, Mom.

378
00:24:41,033 --> 00:24:43,600
I heard Jeffrey
and Coleen talking.

379
00:24:44,167 --> 00:24:46,400
They really don't
want me around.

380
00:24:46,533 --> 00:24:48,933
See? That's exactly what
I warned you about.

381
00:24:49,067 --> 00:24:51,933
Only one more child,
and they'll be complete again.

382
00:24:52,067 --> 00:24:53,500
And if that happens,

383
00:24:53,633 --> 00:24:55,600
they'll erase you
from your father's life.

384
00:24:55,733 --> 00:24:57,700
<i> So you must act.</i>

385
00:24:57,833 --> 00:25:01,300
<i>Do whatever it takes
to stop that annulment.</i>

386
00:25:02,833 --> 00:25:05,067
We need to win your father back.

387
00:25:05,200 --> 00:25:08,467
Jessica, do you hear me?

388
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:10,167
Yes, Mom.

389
00:25:10,833 --> 00:25:12,567
Be brave.

390
00:25:12,700 --> 00:25:17,033
Be like me,
always ready to strike.

391
00:25:17,167 --> 00:25:20,533
How will you fight for
your father if you act weak?

392
00:25:20,667 --> 00:25:22,200
<i> Remember,</i>

393
00:25:22,333 --> 00:25:26,433
we must take your dad back
before he learns the truth.

394
00:25:26,567 --> 00:25:27,900
Understood?

395
00:25:28,333 --> 00:25:29,867
Yes, Mom.

396
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:35,133
Now, wipe those tears
and start fighting.

397
00:25:48,200 --> 00:25:50,333
<i>Mom, Dad, I'm planning
to visit Andrea later.</i>

398
00:25:50,467 --> 00:25:51,900
<i>Please say hi
to her for me, okay?</i>

399
00:25:52,033 --> 00:25:53,867
<i>Tell her she can come home now.</i>

400
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,433
<i>Jessica and I
are leaving anyway.</i>

401
00:25:55,567 --> 00:25:56,400
<i> Please don't leave.</i>

402
00:25:56,533 --> 00:25:57,367
<i> What?</i>

403
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:59,267
<i>If you want to make peac
with your dad,</i>

404
00:25:59,400 --> 00:26:00,367
<i> that's your choice.</i>

405
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:01,933
<i>But maybe if you just
give him a chance...</i>

406
00:26:02,067 --> 00:26:03,833
<i>I've got so much going
on right now, okay?</i>

407
00:26:03,967 --> 00:26:06,267
<i>Things that are way
more important!</i>

408
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,967
<i> We were scammed, Ma'am.</i>

409
00:26:08,100 --> 00:26:10,200
<i>Sis, Mayette invested in it,
too.</i>

410
00:26:10,367 --> 00:26:12,300
<i>How much money
are we talking about here?</i>

411
00:26:12,433 --> 00:26:14,867
<i> 50,000 pesos each.</i>

412
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:19,000
<i>Andrea got caught up in some
investment scam, Jeffrey.</i>

413
00:26:19,133 --> 00:26:19,967
<i> Joel, bro.</i>

414
00:26:20,100 --> 00:26:20,700
<i>What's this rumor
they're spreading</i>

415
00:26:20,833 --> 00:26:21,767
<i> about Andrea on Friendsbook?</i>

416
00:26:21,900 --> 00:26:23,900
<i>Andrea's in trouble,
but she's innocent.</i>

417
00:26:24,033 --> 00:26:25,967
<i> She was also scammed.</i>

418
00:26:27,600 --> 00:26:29,500
<i>Why did you bring
me here, Joel?</i>

419
00:26:29,633 --> 00:26:32,067
<i>I thought we'd go to
your house in Calamba?</i>

420
00:26:32,200 --> 00:26:33,600
<i> Andrea!</i>
